{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":6683,"record_hash":"sha256:a6279e92b931700dd5c88808444671c23084edd68ec7bdf2fea48d03150333cc","timestamp":"2026-05-20T16:14:30.277Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Used `rust-best-practices` lightly for the Rust review lens. No edits made.\\n\\n- **Fix now**: Hook enrichment can mutate GitMeta without syncing.  \\n  [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:74) enriches failed/partial latest turns when duplicate capture has no new records, then returns `0`; [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:120) treats `0 + no association` as “nothing happened” and skips `spawn_agentlog_sync`. Result: hook capture can write environment/index updates locally and never push them.\\n\\n- **Fix now**: Capture holds the agentlog lock before cheap transcript validation.  \\n  [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:158) takes the capture lock, then [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:16) canonicalizes/reads/parses the transcript. Bad/malformed/large transcript input blocks capture/sync and [capture_lock.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture_lock.rs:32) may create storage before validation. Parse the snapshot before locking; recheck/dedupe under lock.\\n\\n- **Document**: Duplicate capture is intentionally not strictly idempotent for incomplete environment snapshots.  \\n  [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:310) can improve failed/partial turns and add index hits even with no new transcript records. That’s reasonable, but the return type/message only says “0 records,” which hides a real write.\\n\\n- **Document**: Enrichment does not refresh session `updated-at`.  \\n  Normal capture updates it at [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:167); enrichment edits at [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:380) skip it. If session lists use update recency, enriched sessions can sort stale.\\n\\n- **Ignore**: Read-order behavior looks deliberate.  \\n  Latest-turn selection uses timestamp plus index tie-break at [mod.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/mod.rs:162); timeline reads sort by timestamp at [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:349). Existing test coverage around reversed stored turn order is pointed at the right behavior.\\n\\nNo tests run; this was review-only as requested.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T16:14:30.277Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}